        }
        .line {
            cursor: pointer;
            padding: 5px;
        }
        .annotation {
            display: none;
            padding: 5px;
            margin-top: 5px;
            background-color: #eef;
            border: 1px solid #ccd;
        }
    </style>
    <script>
        function toggleAnnotation(id) {
            var annotation = document.getElementById(id);
            if (annotation.style.display === "none") {
                annotation.style.display = "block";
            } else {
                annotation.style.display = "none";
            }
        }
    </script>
</head>
<body>

<div class="poem">
    <p class="line" onclick="toggleAnnotation('annotation1')">The cold wind whispers through the night.</p>
    <div class="annotation" id="annotation1">This line uses auditory imagery to evoke a sense of eeriness.</div>

    <p class="line" onclick="toggleAnnotation('annotation2')">Beneath the moon's pale light, shadows dance.</p>
    <div class="annotation" id="annotation2">The phrase "pale light" reflects the Gothic imagery of death and isolation.</div>

    <p class="line" onclick="toggleAnnotation('annotation3')">A lone wolf howls in the distance, lost to time.</p>
    <div class="annotation" id="annotation3">The wolf symbolises isolation and the unknown, a common motif in Gothic poetry.</div>
</div>

